data.title: Pennsylvania American Water offers assistance for customers struggling due to government shutdown, providing payment plans and support.
data.description: In Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania, Pennsylvania American Water is acknowledging the financial difficulties customers may encounter due to the government shutdown. The company is providing various payment plans and assistance programs to aid customers with their water and/or wastewater bills. Gary Lobaugh, the company’s director of government and external affairs, emphasized the company's understanding of the impact the shutdown may have on customers. Pennsylvania American Water aims to support customers by offering help during this challenging time.
